  "text": "Successfully unified the hair positioning system by combining data-offset-y and data-position-y into a single attribute. The new system supports both special cases (like \"between-body-eyes\") and percentage-based positioning (like \"25%\" for 25% down from body top). This makes the API more consistent and intuitive - similar to how data-position-x works with its special cases.\n\nUpdated all components:\n- parse_defs() function to remove offset_y parameter\n- agent_svg() positioning logic to handle percentage parsing\n- Both hair SVG files to use the new unified attributes\n- Documentation in README.md and CLAUDE.md\n\nThe percentage parsing uses simple string detection (endswith(\"%\")) and float conversion, which provides flexible positioning while keeping the implementation straightforward.",
  "sections": [
    "Project Notes"
  ],
